#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Pehle k elements reverse karne hain.
- Baaki elements ka relative order same rehna chahiye.
- Helper Deque use karenge:
  - Front se nikaalenge.
  - Back se wapas daalenge.
- Isse first k elements reverse ho jayenge.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. First k elements queue se nikaal kar helper deque me daalo.
2. Helper ke back se elements nikaal kar queue me daalo.
   - First k elements reverse ho jayenge.
3. Ab reversed elements queue ke rear me hain.
4. Remaining original elements ko front se nikaal kar rear me daalte jao.
5. Is rotation ke baad reversed k elements front par aa jayenge.

📝 EXAMPLE

Queue:
[10,20,30,40,50]
k = 3

Step 1:

Queue:
[40,50]

Helper:
[10,20,30]

----------------

Step 2:
Back se dequeue

30 → Queue
20 → Queue
10 → Queue

Queue:
[40,50,30,20,10]

----------------

Step 3:

diff = 5 - 3 = 2

Rotate 2 times

40 -> rear

Queue:
[50,30,20,10,40]

50 -> rear

Queue:
[30,20,10,40,50]

Final Answer:
[30,20,10,40,50]

❓ WHY HELPER DEQUE
- Queue se sirf front access milta hai.
- Reverse karne ke liye last inserted element pehle chahiye.
- Deque ka pollLast() reverse order provide karta hai.
- Isliye first k elements easily reverse ho jaate hain.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Time  : O(N)

Reason:
- k elements helper me
- k elements wapas queue me
- (n-k) rotations

Total = O(N)

Space : O(K)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Reverse karne ke baad k elements rear me chale jaate hain.
- Isliye rotation step mandatory hai.
- diff = n - k elements ko rotate karke order fix karte hain.
- Pattern:
  Extract → Reverse → Rotate.
- Queue reversal problems me ye bahut common trick hai.

#Code:

import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
	public static Queue<Integer> reverseQueueFirstKElements(int k, Queue<Integer> queue) {
		//You can code here
    if (queue.isEmpty() || k <= 0) return queue;
    int diff = queue.size() - k;

    //Step-1: first k elements dequeue krke helper queue mei daalo
    ArrayDeque<Integer> helper = new ArrayDeque<>();
    for(int i=0; i<k; i++){
      helper.offerLast(queue.poll());
    }

    //step-2: deque ke peeche se nikaalkr queue ke andr enqueue krdo
    while(!helper.isEmpty()){
      queue.offer(helper.pollLast());
    }

    //Step-3: bche hue elements ko ghuma kr peeche le aao
    for(int i=0; i<diff; i++){
      int temp = queue.poll();
      queue.offer(temp);
    }

    return queue;
	}
}
